  "prompt": "What are the best Bank robbery movies?",
  "response": "There are several outstanding bank robbery movies that have captivated audiences over the years with their thrilling plots and intense action. Here are some of the best:\n\n1. **Heat (1995)** - Directed by Michael Mann, this film stars Al Pacino and Robert De Niro and is renowned for its epic heist sequences and deep character development.\n\n2. **Dog Day Afternoon (1975)** - Directed by Sidney Lumet and starring Al Pacino, this film is based on a true story and focuses on a bank robbery that turns into a prolonged hostage situation.\n\n3. **The Town (2010)** - Directed by and starring Ben Affleck, this film is set in Boston and revolves around a group of robbers and their complicated personal lives.\n\n4. **Inside Man (2006)** - Directed by Spike Lee and starring Denzel Washington, Clive Owen, and Jodie Foster, this film features a meticulously planned bank heist and its aftermath.\n\n5. **Point Break (1991)** - Directed by Kathryn Bigelow and starring Keanu Reeves and Patrick Swayze, this film is about a gang of bank robbers who are surfers.\n\n6. **Reservoir Dogs (1992)** - Directed by Quentin Tarantino, this film focuses on the aftermath of a botched robbery and the increasing mistrust among the criminals.\n\n7. **Baby Driver (2017)** - Directed by Edgar Wright, this stylish film follows a getaway driver for a group of bank robbers who wants to leave his life of crime behind.\n\n8. **Ocean's Eleven (2001)** - Directed by Steven Soderbergh and starring George Clooney, Brad Pitt, and Matt Damon, this film involves a meticulously planned casino heist with comedic elements.\n\n9. **Hell or High Water (2016)** - Directed by David Mackenzie and starring Chris Pine and Ben Foster, this film centers around two brothers who rob banks to save their family farm.\n\nThese films are celebrated not only for their thrilling heist sequences but also for their compelling characters and intricate plots.",
